1
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:22,340
(Directed by Li Yuxi)

2
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:27,780
=My Marvellous Fable=

3
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:38,180
=Episode 21=

4
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:43,700
(Go pick up my dad first.)

5
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:45,300
(I still have something to do.)

6
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:46,700
(I'll join you as soon as possible.)

7
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:49,340
I'll get going, then.

8
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:51,420
Let me know once you've arrived.

9
00:01:54,140 --> 00:01:55,700
Do you think
it's a little too sudden for me

10
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,620
to meet your dad like this?

11
00:01:57,540 --> 00:01:58,340
No, it's fine.

12
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:04,540
I'm leaving, then.

13
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:06,260
Okay.

14
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:14,020
Hello?

15
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:15,860
Hello.

16
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:17,540
You must be Mr. Wu, right?

17
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,660
I'm Feng Tianlan.

18
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:19,540
I'm almost there.

19
00:03:19,660 --> 00:03:20,540
Oh, Feng.

20
00:03:21,140 --> 00:03:22,300
Putao informed me earlier.

21
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,260
You can come and find me directly
when you're here.

22
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:25,580
OK.

23
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,820
I'll see you later, then.

24
00:03:34,740 --> 00:03:39,940
(Kangle Nursing Home)

25
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:44,140
(Fortune and misfortune
are often interconnected.)

26
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,260
(When he's questioning me,)

27
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:50,300
(it can also be seen
as me questioning him.)

28
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:57,260
Mr. Wang.

29
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:58,980
(Yes, my surname is Wang.)

30
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,420
(You get one point.)

31
00:04:01,260 --> 00:04:02,540
Can you still remember

32
00:04:02,540 --> 00:04:04,260
what you did yesterday?

33
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,540
(What else could it be?)

34
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:08,420
(You all know what I did.)

35
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,260
Can't you recall anything at all?

36
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,820
Even a small part will do.

37
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:20,700
(Every day is the same.)

38
00:04:21,140 --> 00:04:22,860
(I can even memorize it
backward perfectly.)

39
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,380
(But I won't tell you.)

40
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:30,980
The nurse told me
that you hadn't taken

41
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,380
any of the medication they gave you.

42
00:04:32,580 --> 00:04:34,380
You secretly buried them in the garden.

43
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:38,980
You need to cooperate with us.

44
00:04:39,300 --> 00:04:41,180
Only then can you get better day by day.

45
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:42,180
Am I right?

46
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,300
(They make me take medicine every day)

47
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:45,300
(and make me lie down.)

48
00:04:45,300 --> 00:04:46,700
(Can I even get better?)

49
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:48,740
Don't worry.

50
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,300
We're currently making every effort

51
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,500
to contact your family.

52
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:54,940
(I have a family?)

53
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,540
I...

54
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,300
I...

55
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,740
You remember them?

56
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:08,820
- Ship.
- Ship?

57
00:05:13,540 --> 00:05:14,740
When you were a mariner

58
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:16,140
or when you were a ship captain?

59
00:05:17,820 --> 00:05:19,380
(I was a ship captain?)

60
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:21,980
(Ship)

61
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:26,140
Do you still remember when that was?

62
00:05:32,620 --> 00:05:33,980
The year 2000.

63
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,180
The year 2000?

64
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,820
That was 21 years ago.

65
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,620
Has it been that long?

66
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:40,980
Yes.

67
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,740
You said I have a family.

68
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:52,060
You do.

69
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,620
You have a wife

70
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,700
and a daughter.

71
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:04,260
(Temporal disorientation)
You show good recovery signs today.

72
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,180
If it continues like this,

73
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:07,940
I think...

74
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,940
Why haven't they come to visit me, then?

75
00:06:29,620 --> 00:06:31,180
You've been quite busy lately.

76
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:32,380
Same as always.

77
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:34,940
As for me,

78
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:36,700
I feel like you're all busy

79
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,060
when there are many patients.

80
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,620
I actually wish you weren't busy.

81
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:42,140
If we're not busy,
we'd all be out of jobs.

82
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,500
That would be a good thing.

83
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,380
If you're unemployed,
it can prove one thing.

84
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:46,860
There are fewer patients or no patients.

85
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:47,940
Everyone in the country is healthy.

86
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:49,540
Am I right?

87
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,540
Is he getting any better?

88
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,300
He's still a little confused.

89
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,860
It's a bit worse

90
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:00,860
than when he was first brought here.

91
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,380
But this kind of illness

92
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,060
can only be slowly alleviated.

93
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,820
There's no cure for it.

94
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:09,740
The labor union

95
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,740
just sent off someone last month

96
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:13,380
who was in a similar situation.

97
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:14,980
An elderly person who lived alone.

98
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:21,060
I heard you managed
to contact his daughter.

99
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,060
A young man will come by later.

100
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:26,620
I don't even know how many calls I made.

101
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,260
She only agreed these past two days.

102
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,620
You can imagine
how much resentment there is.

103
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,380
It's been so long,

104
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:37,860
and she doesn't care
about her dad at all.

105
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:41,380
Every family has its own problems.

106
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:42,620
As to what exactly happened,

107
00:07:42,860 --> 00:07:43,740
we don't know, either.

108
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,420
Doctor,

109
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,820
I'd like to know

110
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:32,700
how Mr. Wang Heping's

111
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:33,860
condition is now.

112
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,860
Who are you to him?

113
00:08:39,260 --> 00:08:40,500
His daughter, Wang Putao,

114
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:41,620
is an author.

115
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:42,860
I'm the editor

116
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:44,660
as well as her friend.

117
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:50,500
Wait.

118
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:52,260
That sounds a bit distant.

119
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,340
Her boyfriend?

120
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:03,500
Then why isn't she here, then?

121
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,380
She's occupied with some matters now.

122
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,260
But she'll come later.

123
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:09,780
More precisely, she'll be here tonight.

124
00:09:11,660 --> 00:09:12,860
Then tell her to come herself.

125
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:16,220
But Doctor,

126
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:17,780
it's like this.

127
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:20,580
She entrusted me to visit her father

128
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:22,140
and bring him back to stay
for a couple of days.

129
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:29,260
Wang Heping has Alzheimer's disease.

130
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,140
The hospital requires a direct relative

131
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:34,220
to approve the discharge.

132
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:36,460
What?

133
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:38,740
Doctor, how about...

134
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:42,260
Tell her to come herself.

135
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:45,500
By the way,

136
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:48,220
you should go and visit him now.

137
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,100
No one has visited him in a long time.

138
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:54,820
OK.

139
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,500
(Zhang is exercising.)

140
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:23,460
(They're delivering dinner.)

141
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:32,620
(Another jab coming.)

142
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:35,860
(Great.)

143
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:38,580
(A new day begins.)

144
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,260
(There are people watching everywhere.)

145
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:44,340
(I have no chance to escape.)

146
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:46,260
Wang,

147
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,260
someone is here to visit you.

148
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,620
Who are you?

149
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:04,660
Mr. Wang,

150
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:06,260
I'm your daughter's friend.

151
00:11:07,620 --> 00:11:08,260
Daughter?

152
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:10,580
Yes, your daughter.

153
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:11,860
(Ah, yes.)

154
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,580
(I have a daughter.)

155
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:16,980
Wang,

156
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:20,260
Feng was kind enough
to come all the way here to visit you.

157
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:21,740
Be more friendly to him.

158
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:28,460
I don't know him.

159
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:30,860
Okay.

160
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:32,260
I'll leave you two to it.

161
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:33,900
Thank you.

162
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:41,740
Mr. Wang,

163
00:11:41,980 --> 00:11:43,260
I brought you some fruit.

164
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:57,020
Mr. Wang,

165
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,140
it was Putao...

166
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:00,140
I mean

167
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:01,620
it was Xiwen

168
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,380
who asked me to come
and visit you first.

169
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:08,660
Xiwen?

170
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:10,100
Yes, Xiwen.

171
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:14,380
(Nice.)

172
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:15,860
(My chance is here.)

173
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,340
Mr. Wang,

174
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,500
do you still remember your daughter?

175
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:40,260
Yes.

176
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,380
It's Xiwen.

177
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:45,620
I'm glad you still remember her.

178
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,380
And who are you?

179
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:49,740
I'm her...

180
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:52,140
I'm her friend.

181
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,100
Her friend?

182
00:12:57,860 --> 00:12:58,780
How old are you?

183
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:00,020
I'm 25 this year.

184
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:05,140
He can't be her friend.

185
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:09,020
Xiwen is only 17.

186
00:13:12,220 --> 00:13:13,100
What are you trying to do to her?

187
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:13,620
Who are you?

188
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:14,340
What exactly are you up to, huh?

189
00:13:14,340 --> 00:13:14,860
Mr. Wang,

190
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:15,980
I'm really her friend.

191
00:13:15,980 --> 00:13:16,980
You said you were...

192
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:17,620
I'm 18.

193
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:18,740
I remember now.

194
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:20,220
I'm 18 this year.

195
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:22,260
Please sit down.

196
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:22,980
Here you go.

197
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:24,460
You're 18?

198
00:13:24,660 --> 00:13:25,260
Yes.

199
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:27,780
You look a bit older than that.

200
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,260
You said you're her friend, right?

201
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:34,500
Yes,

202
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:35,460
I'm her friend.

203
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:38,740
How tall are you?

204
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:40,460
I'm 183 cm.

205
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:43,100
You're quite tall.

206
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:48,380
Where are you from?

207
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:49,900
I'm from Shandong.

208
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:55,660
Are your parents still around?

209
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:01,500
Are they in good health?

210
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,260
Do you have any siblings?

211
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:19,780
Will you go back to Shandong
in the future?

212
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:23,580
I would still be working in Beijing.

213
00:14:25,740 --> 00:14:27,740
It's not far away, anyway.

214
00:14:31,780 --> 00:14:32,980
Did you come to see me first,

215
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,900
or did you take her
to visit your parents first?

216
00:14:37,380 --> 00:14:38,340
My parents?

217
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:47,380
Do your parents not support you?

218
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:50,580
They actually want me to go back home.

219
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,140
After all, it's...

220
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:54,500
It doesn't matter.

221
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:55,620
Those things don't matter.

222
00:14:55,860 --> 00:14:57,100
Anyway, I feel that I'm still young

223
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:57,980
and can try different things.

224
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,020
Are you just "trying things" with my daughter?

225
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:03,860
I've been working hard.

226
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:05,020
Especially during this time,

227
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:06,540
your daughter quite trusts me.

228
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,580
She's just a little girl!

229
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:12,060
Mr. Wang.

230
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:14,460
This is a misunderstanding.

231
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:15,100
We misunderstood each other.

232
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:16,180
Misunderstood each other how?

233
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:16,620
No, we didn't.

234
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:17,180
Yes, we did.

235
00:15:17,180 --> 00:15:17,980
We didn't. Not at all.

236
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:18,820
What exactly are you up to?

237
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:19,980
You're just taking advantage of her.

238
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:20,220
No.

239
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:21,580
You're trying
to take advantage of her, right?

240
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:23,100
Your family has found
a future wife for you.

241
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,620
Why are you pestering my daughter, huh?

242
00:15:24,820 --> 00:15:25,740
What are you doing in Beijing, huh?

243
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:27,100
If she's going to Beijing,
what about her study?

244
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:29,580
I begged someone to get her a job.

245
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:30,980
I have been waiting for her to graduate.

246
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:31,460
How could you...

247
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:32,980
You're way older than her.

248
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:33,980
Shameless!

249
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:35,100
How am I being shameless?

250
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:35,820
I'm not.

251
00:15:35,820 --> 00:15:36,820
Xiwen is only 17.

252
00:15:36,820 --> 00:15:38,460
She passed the age of 27 long ago!

253
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:39,340
What? 27?

254
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:40,820
She's already in her thirties.

255
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:42,100
Why are you and your daughter

256
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:42,980
the same?

257
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:43,580
Starting an argument

258
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:44,180
whenever you want to.

259
00:15:44,180 --> 00:15:45,300
You're both so unreasonable.

260
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:49,940
Xiwen...

261
00:15:50,980 --> 00:15:52,580
She's over 30 already?

262
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,460
Xiwen is over 30.

263
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:01,980
I have to go home and cook.

264
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:04,100
Xiwen will come home from school soon.

265
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:05,620
I must cook something for her.

266
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:07,180
I must tell you

267
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,420
the food here is terrible.

268
00:16:08,420 --> 00:16:08,700
I'm serious.

269
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:10,460
My daughter can't eat the food here.

270
00:16:10,820 --> 00:16:10,980
Oh,

271
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:12,340
how did you come here?

272
00:16:12,340 --> 00:16:13,740
Can we get home by bus?

273
00:16:14,820 --> 00:16:16,060
I drove here.

274
00:16:16,460 --> 00:16:17,220
That's great.

275
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,500
Thank you, Mr. Ma.

276
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:21,460
My surname is Feng.

277
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,820
Do you prefer the surname, Feng?

278
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:35,180
(This is outrageous)

279
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,460
(and it seems so familiar.)

280
00:16:37,980 --> 00:16:38,340
This way.

281
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:40,180
(I had the same feeling)

282
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,700
(when Wang Putao asked me)

283
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,700
(to drive her back to Hainan.)

284
00:17:01,340 --> 00:17:01,860
Let's go.

285
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,100
Go downstairs.

286
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:07,500
Don't run.

287
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:08,140
Watch your steps.

288
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:10,980
Be careful.

289
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:17,020
This way.

290
00:17:20,860 --> 00:17:21,100
Wait.

